  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sahel: investigating violations/abuses by State security forces and armed groups in the Liptako Gourma region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">During the past decade, the Western Sahel has become a hotbed of instability in sub-Saharan Africa. From Mali through Burkina Faso to Chad and Niger, violent extremism together with community conflicts over access to resources have swept through the region. This has been accompanied by serious human rights violations and abuses on civilian populations often caught in the cross fire of the conflict.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Burkina Faso and Mali, the main aim of the Liptako Gourma or &#x2018;Sahel&#x2019; project was to contribute to strengthening the protection of human rights through monitoring violations and abuses committed by State security forces and armed groups.  Specifically, on both sides of the border, the project objectives were to:

&#x2022; Strengthen the capacities of human rights organizations and field monitors on Monitoring, Documentation and Reporting (MDR) techniques in order to document human rights violations in their communities;
&#x2022; Support local partners in the documentation and reporting on cases of human rights violations and abuses linked to the security crisis in Burkina, particularly in the North, Center-North regions and the Sahel;
&#x2022; Contribute to the respect for human rights through targeted advocacy.

The project laid the foundation for future work on the Sahel under the Power of Voices framework.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the wake of intensifying armed conflict in the Liptako Gourma region, which is the border area between Mali, Burkina Faso and Niger, AINL/HURICAP is seeking to strengthen human rights defenders operating in this region so that they can properly investigate and document the human rights violations that are committed in the context of the conflict. To this end, our local partner in Mali undertook a baseline study in 2020 that elucidates the underlying problems that need to be addressed to protect human rights and restoring security in its border regions. Simultaneously, AINL/HURICAP was supporting a project to monitor violations and abuses committed by State security forces and armed groups in Burkina Faso&#x2019;s North, Centre-North and Sahel regions.</narrative>
  </description>
